    "teacher_markdown": "**Error Type**: Syntax Error (Code won’t run due to a typo)\r\n\r\n**Expected Outcome**: The `Painter` should move forward and paint a red and green tile.\r\n\r\nDebugging Challenge\r\n\r\n- The program throws an `AttributeError` because `.painter()` and `.pant()` are not a valid `Painter` methods.\r\n- Students must determine what’s wrong with these method calls and correct them.\r\n- Hint for students: Carefully check function and method names.",
    "bubble_choice_description": "You’re sure you wrote everything correctly, but your program refuses to run. There’s an issue hiding in plain sight — something small but critical is causing everything to break. Can you spot the problem?",
    "thumbnail_url": "https://images.code.org/90ca4a7e331a1716e0aea9c488104d91-virus-scan.png",
    "display_name": "Debugging Challenge 4",
    "validation_file": {
      "id": "2",
      "name": "main_test.py",
      "language": "py",
      "contents": "import unittest\nfrom unittest_runner import ValidationProtocol\n\nclass TestPainterReachesCone(unittest.TestCase):\n    @classmethod\n    def setUpClass(cls):\n        \"\"\"\n        Retrieve the NeighborhoodLog once for all tests.\n        \"\"\"\n        cls.neighborhood_log = ValidationProtocol().get_neighborhood_log()\n        painter_logs = cls.neighborhood_log.painter_logs\n        cls.painter_log = painter_logs[0] if painter_logs else None\n\n    def test_step1_create_painter(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Create a Painter object.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.assertIsNotNone(\n            self.painter_log,\n            \"We couldn't find a Painter object. Make sure you create one!\"\n        )\n\n    def test_step2_final_position(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Painter moves to the other end.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.painter_log is None:\n            self.skipTest(\"No Painter found!\")\n\n        final_pos = self.painter_log.ending_position\n        if final_pos.x != 7 or final_pos.y != 0:\n            self.fail(\n                \"Your Painter should move to the other end.\"\n            )\n",
      "folderId": "0",
